  "prompt": "How much does it cost to make a music video?",
  "response": "The cost of making a music video can vary widely depending on various factors such as the production quality, location, talent, crew, equipment, and post-production work. Here are some general cost estimates:\n\n1. **Low-budget music videos** - These can cost anywhere from $1,000 to $10,000. These might involve simple setups, minimal special effects, and using local talent and locations.\n\n2. **Mid-range budget music videos** - Typically range from $10,000 to $50,000. These can include more professional production quality, better equipment, more elaborate sets, special effects, and possibly hiring professional actors and dancers.\n\n3. **High-budget and professional music videos** - These can cost from $50,000 to several hundred thousand dollars. These videos might include high-end production quality, famous directors, elaborate sets and costumes, special effects, and high-profile talent.\n\n4. **Major label production videos** - Top-tier productions can easily exceed $1 million, particularly if they involve well-known artists, extended shoot locations, high-end post-production, and significant promotional efforts.\n\nIt's important to note that the cost can also be influenced by factors such as the complexity of the concept, the duration of the shoot, specific technical requirements, and the artist or band's popularity and demands.",
